  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stop the Spread COVID-19, Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of Amref&apos;s co-ordinated response to Stop the Spread and Flatten the Curve in 8 priority countries across Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to train community health workers (CHWs) and healthcare professionals (HCPs) using Amref&apos;s mobile digital platforms (LEAP and JIBU) on a MoH approved curriculum for COVID-19. This covers key relevant topics such as home-based care and  monitoring tools (for CHWs) and infection, prevention, control measures and rapid response for COVID-19 (for HCPs).


The project also aims to support mental health initiatives including a mental health training manual and key messages.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will train 2,000 HCPs and 4,500 CHWs</narrative>
  </description>
